We ve collected your feedback over the past few months and combined it into this update. Twiq 3.0 includes a brand new feed where you can talk publicly with other users. You can create posts and comments vote or simply mark your favorite posts. There is also a new coin system. This brings you many advantages. You can use your coins where you like it the most and have for example more requests or likes per day than before. If you collect upvotes on your posts or comments you will even receive additional coins. In addition to the changes mentioned here we have made many other minor improvements and bug fixes. We hope you like the app even more now and we wish you a lot of fun with it.
We have fixed the bug that when resetting requests requests to users who had denied the request were sometimes not reset correctly.
Bug fixes and performance improvements

The vicinity list can be sorted by online status and now also by distance. The distance is displayed in requests from the vicinity list. Requests can be limited by activating the request filter. Power Booster can be used in the vicinity list and in Twiq Live. There is the possibility to reset all requests. Bug fixes and performance improvements
Now you can filter and sort likes. Bug fixes and performance improvements

We have integrated several new features into Twiq and are happy to finally make them available to you. Below are the most important new features: Twiq Match: Find chat partners with the same interests. Twiq Profile: Create a Twiq profile and view the Twiq profiles of your chat partners. Power Booster: Send a message together with your request.
Bug fixes and performance improvements
